#DESCRIPTION
#  Find 2 critical point of a cubic polynomial and determine
#  whether the polynomial increases or decreases on the intervals
#  involving the critical points.
#ENDDESCRIPTION
## DBsubject(Calculus - single variable)
## DBchapter(Applications of differentiation)
## DBsection(Increasing/decreasing functions and local extrema)
## Date(6/3/2002)
## Institution(Univeristy of Utah)
## Author(Utah ww group)
## Level(3)
## TitleText1('Calculus')
## AuthorText1('Dale Varberg, Edwin J. Purcell, and Steven E. Rigdon')
## EditionText1('9')
## Section1('Applications of the Derivative')
## Problem1('')
## TitleText2('Calculus: Early Transcendentals')
## AuthorText2('Rogawski')
## EditionText2('1')
## Section2('4.3')
## Problem2('29')
## TitleText3('Calculus: Early Transcendentals')
## AuthorText3('Stewart')
## EditionText3('6')
## Section3('4.3')
## Problem3('11')
## KEYWORDS('calculus','Graph', 'Critical', 'Increasing', 'Decreasing','Derivatives', 'critical points', 'minimum,maximum')

DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
  "PGstandard.pl",
  "PGchoicemacros.pl",
  "PGcourse.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(1,5,1);
$b1 = random(6,10,1);
$coef3 = 2;
$coef2 = 3*($a1+$b1);
$coef1 = 6*$a1*$b1;
$coef0 = random(1,11,1);

TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Consider the function \( f(x) = -$coef3 x^3 + $coef2 x^2 - $coef1 x + $coef0 \).
For this function there are three important intervals:
 \( (-\infty, A] \), \( [A,B] \), and \( [B,\infty) \) where
 \( A \) and  \( B \) are the critical points
$BR
Find \( A \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = $a1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
and  \( B \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = $b1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
For each of the following intervals, tell whether \( f(x) \)
is increasing (type in INC) or decreasing (type in DEC).
$BR
\( (-\infty, A] \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "DEC";
ANS(str_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( [A,B] \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "INC";
ANS(str_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( [B,\infty) \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "DEC";
ANS(str_cmp($ans));
ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
